    "description_long": "This bus shelter features a sturdy metal frame with a curved, semi-transparent roof, providing protection from the elements. The shelter has three side panels: one with a blue caution-patterned covering, another with a large graffiti tag, and a third displaying a route map and a notice. A bench is integrated along the back wall, offering seating for waiting passengers. The shelter includes a round route sign labeled 'A-7' mounted on one corner, enhancing visibility for approaching commuters. The overall structure is weathered, with visible signs of urban wear such as graffiti and posted notices, giving it an authentic city street appearance.",
